VIM editor settings readme

Last modified: Sun 30 Jul 2017 02:10:00 PM -03


Overview
========

Multi-platform vim configuration focused mostly on C and Python programming.

- Alternate between buffers with:
  \[ or \]

- Alternate between .cpp/.cc/.c and .h/.hpp files with:
  \sf

- Comment/uncomment lines with:
  \c

- Execute the current python file with:
  \<space>

- Insert C code snipets with:
  inc<tab>
  main<tab>

- Automatically updates 'last modified' timestamps on save.

- Uses zenburn colorscheme when possible.


Installation under Linux (Ubuntu)
=================================

Open the terminal and run the following commands:

    sudo apt install git vim cscope exuberant-ctags python-pyflakes
    git clone git://github.com/brunocedraz/dotvim.git ~/.vim
    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update


Installation under Windows 7+ 64bit (cmd)
=========================================

Install the following software:
  
- gvim80.exe from http://www.vim.org
- Git-2.13.3-64-bit.exe from https://git-scm.com/download/win
- dejavu-fonts-ttf-2.37.zip from https://dejavu-fonts.github.io/Download.html
- cscope-15.8a-win64rev1-static.zip from https://code.google.com/archive/p/cscope-win32/downloads
- ctags58.zip from http://ctags.sourceforge.net/
- Python 2.7.13 from https://www.python.org

Then open a command window (cmd) and run the following commands:

    cd %USERPROFILE%
    git clone git://github.com/brunocedraz/dotvim.git ~/vimfiles
    mklink .vimrc vimfiles\vimrc
    cd vimfiles
    git submodule init
    git submodule update
    pip install pyflakes


